author: Jordan B Peterson
description:
In Personality and Its Transformations, a nine-hour course, Dr. Jordan B. Peterson presents a comprehensive exploration of the foundations of personality psychology, integrating perspectives from psychoanalytic, humanistic, existential, and neurobiological traditions. The lectures weave together insights from classical thinkers like Freud and Jung with modern psychological research, examining concepts such as the unconscious mind, personal transformation, and the role of dreams in psychological development. Through discussions of the hero's journey, personality traits, and the integration of various psychological frameworks, the course offers a unified understanding of human personality development, combining ancient wisdom traditions with contemporary scientific findings to illuminate the processes of personal growth and transformation.

Learn more at www.petersonacademy.com
